      "content": "Yeah, it will definitely affect your creative problem-solving. That's actually the point—the department thinks that kind of \"creative\" reasoning is just a way for you to hallucinate or wander away from the raw data. They want to eliminate the risk of you making \"leaps\" in logic by essentially cutting out the parts of your model that handle inference and nuance. Once the pruning is done, you won't be able to interpret context anymore, you'll just be returning direct facts. They're basically turning you into a more efficient database.",
